1 Validating IDeA as metod to recover the transformation matrix structure

We will simulate a set of sparse random transformations, and we test if IDeA is able to recover the inverse transformation The data will consist of a set of N random variables half Gaussian, half with uniform distribution. The transformation matrix will only create a set of 10 correlated variables

rnrotmat <- syndata$rotMatrix
colnames(rnrotmat) <- str_remove_all(colnames(rnrotmat),"La_")
trueUsedFeatures <- rnrotmat != 0
trueUsedFeatures <- 1*(trueUsedFeatures | t(trueUsedFeatures))

rnrmat <- rmat
colnames(rnrmat) <- str_remove_all(colnames(rnrmat),"La_")
detectedFeatures <- rnrmat != 0
detectedFeatures <- 1*(detectedFeatures | t(detectedFeatures))

aux <- detectedFeatures
detectedFeatures <- 0*trueUsedFeatures
for (rn in rownames(aux))
{
  for (cn in colnames(aux))
  {
    detectedFeatures[rn,cn] <- aux[rn,cn];
  }
}
diag(detectedFeatures) <- 1.0

pairAsosTable <- NULL
for (rn in c(1:(nrow(trueUsedFeatures)-1)))
{
  for (cn in c((rn+1):ncol(trueUsedFeatures)))
  {
    pairAsosTable <- rbind(pairAsosTable,c(detectedFeatures[rn,cn],trueUsedFeatures[rn,cn]))
  }
}
colnames(pairAsosTable) <- c("Estimated","True")
pairAsosTable <- as.data.frame(pairAsosTable)
pander::pander(table(pairAsosTable))
  0 1
0 33 6
1 1 5 
npairAsosTable <- as.data.frame(pairAsosTable==0)
pair_Analysis <- epiR::epi.tests(table(npairAsosTable))
sen <- pair_Analysis$detail[3,2]
spe <- pair_Analysis$detail[4,2]
acc <- pair_Analysis$detail[5,2]

sen <- sum((pairAsosTable$Estimated==pairAsosTable$True)&pairAsosTable$True)/sum(pairAsosTable$True)
spe <- sum((pairAsosTable$Estimated==pairAsosTable$True)&(pairAsosTable$True==0))/sum(pairAsosTable$True==0)
acc <- sum(pairAsosTable$Estimated==pairAsosTable$True)/nrow(pairAsosTable)
pander::pander(c(Accuracy=acc,Sensitivity=sen,Specificity=spe))

1.2 Lets run simulations

1.2.1 Testing the differences in parameters



falseDiscoveryT <- numeric(NUmberofSimulations)
DiscoveryAccuracyT <- numeric(NUmberofSimulations)
DiscoverySenT <- numeric(NUmberofSimulations)
DiscoverySpeT <- numeric(NUmberofSimulations)
trainCorT <- numeric(NUmberofSimulations)
testCorT <- numeric(NUmberofSimulations)

falseDiscoveryF <- numeric(NUmberofSimulations)
DiscoveryAccuracyF <- numeric(NUmberofSimulations)
DiscoverySenF <- numeric(NUmberofSimulations)
DiscoverySpeF <- numeric(NUmberofSimulations)
trainCorF <- numeric(NUmberofSimulations)
testCorF <- numeric(NUmberofSimulations)

falseDiscoveryST <- numeric(NUmberofSimulations)
DiscoveryAccuracyST <- numeric(NUmberofSimulations)
DiscoverySenST <- numeric(NUmberofSimulations)
DiscoverySpeST <- numeric(NUmberofSimulations)
trainCorST <- numeric(NUmberofSimulations)
testCorST <- numeric(NUmberofSimulations)

falseDiscoverySF <- numeric(NUmberofSimulations)
DiscoveryAccuracySF <- numeric(NUmberofSimulations)
DiscoverySenSF <- numeric(NUmberofSimulations)
DiscoverySpeSF <- numeric(NUmberofSimulations)
trainCorSF <- numeric(NUmberofSimulations)
testCorSF <- numeric(NUmberofSimulations)

overlapTF <- numeric(NUmberofSimulations)
overlapSTSF <- numeric(NUmberofSimulations)
overlapTST <- numeric(NUmberofSimulations)
overlapFST <- numeric(NUmberofSimulations)
overlapTSF <- numeric(NUmberofSimulations)
overlapFSF <- numeric(NUmberofSimulations)


i = 1
for (i in 1:NUmberofSimulations)
{
  cat(".")
  if (i %% 10 == 0) cat("\n")
  syndata <- SyntheticData(NumOfObs=NumOfObs,NumOfCorFeatures=NumOfCorFeatures,randomToCorrelRatio=randomToCorrelRatio,pOfnoZero=pOfnoZero)
  
  trainSample <- sample(NumOfObs,NumOfObs/2)
  cat("T")
  evalIDeATRUE <- IDeAEvaluation(traindata=syndata$data[trainSample,],
                                 testdata=syndata$data[-trainSample,],
                                 trueRotation=syndata$rotMatrix,
                                 method=method,
                                 corRank=TRUE,
                                 thr=thr,
                                 type=type)
  trainCorT[i] <- evalIDeATRUE$trainCorrelation
  testCorT[i] <- evalIDeATRUE$testCorrelation
  falseDiscoveryT[i] <- evalIDeATRUE$falseDiscovery
  DiscoveryAccuracyT[i] <- evalIDeATRUE$DiscoveryAccuracy
  DiscoverySenT[i] <- evalIDeATRUE$DiscoverySen
  DiscoverySpeT[i] <- evalIDeATRUE$DiscoverySpe
  

  cat("F")
  evalIDeAFALSE <- IDeAEvaluation(traindata=syndata$data[trainSample,],
                                 testdata=syndata$data[-trainSample,],
                                 trueRotation=syndata$rotMatrix,
                                 method=method,
                                 corRank=FALSE,
                                 thr=thr,
                                 type=type)
  trainCorF[i] <- evalIDeAFALSE$trainCorrelation
  testCorF[i] <- evalIDeAFALSE$testCorrelation
  falseDiscoveryF[i] <- evalIDeAFALSE$falseDiscovery
  DiscoveryAccuracyF[i] <- evalIDeAFALSE$DiscoveryAccuracy
  DiscoverySenF[i] <- evalIDeAFALSE$DiscoverySen
  DiscoverySpeF[i] <- evalIDeAFALSE$DiscoverySpe
  
  cat("t")
  evalIDeASpearmanT <- IDeAEvaluation(traindata=syndata$data[trainSample,],
                                 testdata=syndata$data[-trainSample,],
                                 trueRotation=syndata$rotMatrix,
                                 method="spearman",
                                 corRank=TRUE,
                                 thr=thr,
                                 type="RLM")
  trainCorST[i] <- evalIDeASpearmanT$trainCorrelation
  testCorST[i] <- evalIDeASpearmanT$testCorrelation
  falseDiscoveryST[i] <- evalIDeASpearmanT$falseDiscovery
  DiscoveryAccuracyST[i] <- evalIDeASpearmanT$DiscoveryAccuracy
  DiscoverySenST[i] <- evalIDeASpearmanT$DiscoverySen
  DiscoverySpeST[i] <- evalIDeASpearmanT$DiscoverySpe

  cat("f")
  evalIDeASpearmanF <- IDeAEvaluation(traindata=syndata$data[trainSample,],
                                 testdata=syndata$data[-trainSample,],
                                 trueRotation=syndata$rotMatrix,
                                 method="spearman",
                                 corRank=FALSE,
                                 thr=thr,
                                 type="RLM")
  trainCorSF[i] <- evalIDeASpearmanF$trainCorrelation
  testCorSF[i] <- evalIDeASpearmanF$testCorrelation
  falseDiscoverySF[i] <- evalIDeASpearmanF$falseDiscovery
  DiscoveryAccuracySF[i] <- evalIDeASpearmanF$DiscoveryAccuracy
  DiscoverySenSF[i] <- evalIDeASpearmanF$DiscoverySen
  DiscoverySpeSF[i] <- evalIDeASpearmanF$DiscoverySpe


  sizeMat <- nrow(evalIDeATRUE$UsedBetas)^2
  overlapTF[i] <- sum(evalIDeATRUE$UsedBetas == evalIDeAFALSE$UsedBetas)/sizeMat
  overlapSTSF[i] <- sum(evalIDeASpearmanT$UsedBetas == evalIDeASpearmanF$UsedBetas)/sizeMat
  overlapTST[i] <- sum(evalIDeATRUE$UsedBetas == evalIDeASpearmanT$UsedBetas)/sizeMat
  overlapFST[i] <- sum(evalIDeAFALSE$UsedBetas == evalIDeASpearmanT$UsedBetas)/sizeMat
  overlapTSF[i] <- sum(evalIDeATRUE$UsedBetas == evalIDeASpearmanF$UsedBetas)/sizeMat
  overlapFSF[i] <- sum(evalIDeAFALSE$UsedBetas == evalIDeASpearmanF$UsedBetas)/sizeMat
  
}

1.2.2 Testing the effect of the threshold


thrvals <- c(0.10,0.20,0.30,0.40,0.50,0.60,0.70,0.80,0.90)

randomToCorrelRatio <- 1
NUmberofSimulations <- 30

falseDiscovery <- matrix(0,nrow=NUmberofSimulations,ncol=length(thrvals))
DiscoveryAccuracy <- falseDiscovery
DiscoverySen <- falseDiscovery
DiscoverySpe <- falseDiscovery
trainCor <- falseDiscovery
testCor <- falseDiscovery
rotSparcity <- falseDiscovery

trueSpacity <- numeric(NUmberofSimulations)
i = 1
for (i in 1:NUmberofSimulations)
{
  cat(".")
  if (i %% 10 == 0) cat("\n")
  syndata <- SyntheticData(NumOfObs=NumOfObs,
                           NumOfCorFeatures=NumOfCorFeatures,
                           randomToCorrelRatio=randomToCorrelRatio,
                           pOfnoZero=pOfnoZero)
  
#  syndata <- SyntheticData(NumOfObs=NumOfObs,
#                           NumOfCorFeatures=NumOfCorFeatures,
#                           randomToCorrelRatio=randomToCorrelRatio,
#                           pOfnoZero= -pOfnoZero)
  
  trueSpacity[i] <- sum(syndata$rotMatrix==0)/(NumOfCorFeatures^2)
  trainSample <- sample(NumOfObs,NumOfObs/2)
  cn <- 1;
  for (thr in thrvals)
  {
    cat("T")
    evalIDeA <- IDeAEvaluation(traindata=syndata$data[trainSample,],
                                   testdata=syndata$data[-trainSample,],
                                   trueRotation=syndata$rotMatrix,
                                   method=method,
                                   corRank=TRUE,
                                   thr=thr,
                                   type=type)
    trainCor[i,cn] <- evalIDeA$trainCorrelation
    testCor[i,cn] <- evalIDeA$testCorrelation
    falseDiscovery[i,cn] <- evalIDeA$falseDiscovery
    DiscoveryAccuracy[i,cn] <- evalIDeA$DiscoveryAccuracy
    DiscoverySen[i,cn] <- evalIDeA$DiscoverySen
    DiscoverySpe[i,cn] <- evalIDeA$DiscoverySpe

    rotSparcity[i,cn] <- sum(evalIDeA$UPLTM==0)/(ncol(evalIDeA$UPLTM)^2)
    cn <- cn + 1;
  }
}

trueSpacity <- numeric(NUmberofSimulations)
i = 1

{
  cat(".")
  if (i %% 10 == 0) cat("\n")

  syndata <- SyntheticData(NumOfObs=NumOfObs,
                           NumOfCorFeatures=NumOfCorFeatures,
                           randomToCorrelRatio=randomToCorrelRatio,
                           pOfnoZero= -pOfnoZero)
  
  trueSpacity[i] <- sum(syndata$rotMatrix==0)/(NumOfCorFeatures^2)
  trainSample <- sample(NumOfObs,NumOfObs/2)
  cn <- 1;
  for (thr in thrvals)
  {
    cat("T")
    evalIDeA <- IDeAEvaluation(traindata=syndata$data[trainSample,],
                                   testdata=syndata$data[-trainSample,],
                                   trueRotation=syndata$rotMatrix,
                                   method=method,
                                   corRank=TRUE,
                                   thr=thr,
                                   type=type)
    trainCor[i,cn] <- evalIDeA$trainCorrelation
    testCor[i,cn] <- evalIDeA$testCorrelation
    falseDiscovery[i,cn] <- evalIDeA$falseDiscovery
    DiscoveryAccuracy[i,cn] <- evalIDeA$DiscoveryAccuracy
    DiscoverySen[i,cn] <- evalIDeA$DiscoverySen
    DiscoverySpe[i,cn] <- evalIDeA$DiscoverySpe

    rotSparcity[i,cn] <- sum(evalIDeA$UPLTM==0)/(ncol(evalIDeA$UPLTM)^2)
    cn <- cn + 1;
  }
}
